<main id="main">
    <h1>Setting up Mediamarkt</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph previous-next-navigation">
<p><a href="/en/markets/mediamarkt/first-steps"><span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-left  "></i></span> First steps</a>
<a href="/en/markets/mediamarkt/automatic-data-exchange"><span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-long-arrow-left  "></i></span> Automatic product and offer data exchange </a></p>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Learn on this page how to set up the interface to Mediamarkt. First, you have to carry out some preparatory settings in your plentymarkets system.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="order-referrer">1. Activating the order referrer</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>An order referrer tags an order with the sales channel on which the order was generated. You also need to activate the order referrer in order to link items, characteristics etc. with Mediamarkt. Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong> to activate the order referrer.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activating the order referrer for Mediamarkt:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Order referrer</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the referrer <strong>{market}</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="sales-price">2. Defining a sales price</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Sales prices define the conditions under which a variation is sold at a specific price and on a specific sales channel. That means that to sell variations on Mediamarkt, you need a sales price in which the order referrer Mediamarkt is activated. The price that you save for this sales price is the price that will be shown on Mediamarkt.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Defining a sales price for Mediamarkt:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Item » Sales prices » [Open sales price]</strong>.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> No sales prices? Then create a <a href="/en/item/settings/prices#100">new sales price</a> first.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the referrer <strong>Mediamarkt</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the referrer <strong>Mirakl</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="create-properties">3. Creating properties</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Using properties, you can export fields to the marketplace that aren’t defined in plentymarkets by default.
You can create the properties that are specified by Mediamarkt in the <strong>Setup » Settings » Properties » Configuration</strong> menu.
For further information on properties, refer to the <a href="/en/item/settings/properties#500">Characteristics and properties</a> page.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For Mediamarkt, you need the following properties:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Logistics class</p>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>This is the link of a variation with a certain market shipping profile. You can see the market shipping profiles in the market back end in the <strong>Platform settings &gt; Shipping</strong> menu. The value in brackets is the value that has to be transferred.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p>Leadtime to ship</p>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The so-called <em>leadtime-to-ship</em> is the time that a seller needs from the order acceptance to the shipping registration. Here, a whole number between 1 and 45 has to be transferred.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<p>update-delete</p>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The option to delete an offer. If no value is selected at the variation, the market used <code>update</code> by default.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<h3 id="_creating_the_logistics_class_property" class="discrete">Creating the logistics class property</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For each variation, you need to export a shipping profile code to Mediamarkt. You can configure shipping profiles in the Mirakl back end. For a list of shipping profiles, refer to the <strong>Platform settings &gt; Shipping</strong> menu in the Mirakl back end. You can find the code in the <strong>Logistics class</strong> column in brackets behind the name of the logistics class.</p>
</div>
